cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the automated selection and placement of images in a multimodal story, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) for object recognition, information retrieval (cs.IR) for selecting relevant images, natural language processing (cs.CL) for understanding the context of the story, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the unsupervised combinatorial optimization. Additionally, the paper focuses on multimodal contents (cs.MM) which is the overarching category for this research.
